<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agriculture Delegates Visit Thailand, Malaysia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3003115494 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1300 GMT 29 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Myanmar [Burma] delegation led by Deputy 
Agriculture Minister U Tin Hlaing and five others left Yangon 
[Rangoon] for Thailand by air at 1640. They will study 
agricultural activities under the Thai-Myanmar bilateral 
technical cooperation program at the invitation of the Thai 
Government. Then they will travel to Malaysia to study 
agriculture, rubber, palm oil, tropical fruits, vegetables, and 
other horticultural activities. The delegation was seen off at 
the airport by Agriculture Minister Lieutenant General Myint 
Aung, Deputy Agriculture Minister U Kyaw Tin, and responsible 
personnel. 

</TEXT>

