<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   NCGUB Says Missing Minister in `SLORC Hands' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3103100994 Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma in Burmese 1430 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3103100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Democratic Voice of Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dear listeners: The National Coalition Government 
of the Union of Burma [NCGUB] issued a statement today saying it 
has received news that U Myint Maung, a NCGUB minister who has 
been reported missing since 25 March, is in the hands of the 
SLORC [State Law and Order Restoration Council]. 
  The statement says U Myint Maung, NCGUB minister of 
agriculture and forests, disappeared on 25 March while en route 
from Chiang Mai to Bangkok. When the NCGUB began investigating 
the disappearance, it received news he had fallen into SLORC 
hands. U Myint Maung was elected as a representative from Einme 
Township constituency 2, Irrawaddy Division in the 1990 
elections. 
  Similarly, two NCGUB ministers -- Minister U Win Ko and 
Minister U Hla Pe -- were assassinated while traveling in 1993. 
The NCGUB is highly suspicious of the SLORC's role in the two 
murders and the recent disappearance of Minister U Myint Maung. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

