<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Cites Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3003151394 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1300 GMT 30 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brigadier General Abel, minister of national 
planning and economic development, explained the situation of 
Myanmar's [Burma] economic developments to visiting prime 
minister of Singapore, Mr. Goh Chok Tong, his delegation, and 
the Singaporean businessmen who accompanied the prime minister, 
at the International Business Center on Prome Road, Yangon 
[Rangoon], at 0900 this morning. 
  The ceremony was attended by Deputy Prime Minister Vice 
Admiral Maung Maung Khin; Forestry Affairs Minister Lieutenant 
General Chit Swe; Hotels and Tourism Minister Lt. Gen. Kyaw Ba; 
Livestock Breeding and Fisheries Minister Brig. Gen. Maung 
Maung; Finance and Revenue Minister Brig. Gen. Win Tin; 
Communications, Post, and Telegraphs Minister U Soe Tha; deputy 
ministers; Myanmar Ambassador U Phone Myint; Charge d'Affaires U 
Kyaw Myint; responsible personnel from the Foreign Ministry; and 
invited guests. 
  Firstly, Brig. Gen. Abel explained the structure of Myanmar 
and its natural resources, prevailing economic development 
situation, figures relating to economic and social activities, 
foreign investment situation and opportunities, and Myanmar's 
economic developments. 
  Next, Minister Brig. Gen. Abel and Minister Brig. Gen. Win 
Tin answered queries raised by the visiting prime minister, his 
delegation, and the Singaporean businessmen. 

</TEXT>

