<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Convention Session Continues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3103093294 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 0630 GMT 31 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3103093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Burmese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Convention Plenary Session continued at 
0900 this morning in the Central Meeting Hall of the President's 
Residence compound on Ahlone Road, Yangon [Rangoon]. 
  The plenary session was attended by Lieutenant General Myo 
Nyunt, chairman of the National Convention Convening Commission, 
Vice Chairmen Lt. Gen. Maung Thint and Brigadier General Myo 
Thant, and commission members; U Aung Toe, chairman of the 
National Convention Convening Work Committee [NCCWC], Vice 
Chairman U Tha Tun, and work committee members; Brig. Gen. Tin 
Aye, chairman of the National Convention Convening Management 
Committee, and committee members; delegates; and local and 
foreign correspondents. 
  U Tin Maung of the delegate group representing technocrats 
and the intelligentsia acted as alternate chairperson of the 
plenary session. Dr. Than Nyunt, Daw May Than Lwin, U San Tha 
Aung, U Mahn Ohn Maung, U Kan Nyunt, U Soe Maung, U Khin Maung 
Htoo, and U Sai Aung Htun acted as members of the Panel of 
Chairmen. U Khin Maung Myint, director general of the NCCWC 
Office and the official in charge of meetings, acted as 
secretary of the meeting. 
  First, the secretary of the meeting announced the session 
was 
valid because 654 of the 694 delegates were in attendance. 
According to the agenda, delegates from the delegate group 
representing elected representatives read proposals on 
suggestions to prescribe fundamental principles related to the 
state, state structure, and head of state chapters that will be 
included in drawing up the constitution. At the plenary 
session, Dr. Thein Lwin; U Tun Aung, alias U Tun Tun Hein; U Saw 
Oo Reh; and U Hla Min -- representing the National League for 
Democracy in the elected representatives delegate group -- read 
proposal reports. 
  The plenary session recessed at 1120. 
  The afternoon session of the National Convention Plenary 
Session is in progress at the Central Meeting Hall of the 
President's Residence compound on Ahlone Road, Yangon. 

</TEXT>

