<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knin Rally Against UNPROFOR Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502141994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1322 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 25 Feb (TANJUG) -- Due to the full blockade of 
western Slavonia, which is still in progress, protest meetings 
were held in the republic of Serb Krajina today where citizens 
and young people expressed displeasure and indignation over 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] behavior. 
  Several thousand citizens of Knin spontaneously rallied in 
the square in front of the railway station in the Krajina 
capital this morning. The rally was addressed by members of the 
Citizens' Protest committee and representatives of other 
citizens' and youth organizations. 
  "Our freedom is being threatened, world powers wish to 
transform us into a camp," this is only one of the messages that 
were voiced at this rally. 
  The attitude of the citizens of Krajina is best reflected in 
placards carried by young citizens of Knin: "We cannot give up 
western Slavonia," "Protection yes, occupation no," "UNPROFOR, 
go to the Croatian border." 
  Similar messages were voiced at other rallies in Krajina, in 
Vojnic, Benkovac, and other towns where strong support was 
voiced for Milan Martic, the president of the republic of Serb 
Krajina, to defend Krajina's sovereignty in talks with UN 
special envoy Yasushi Akashi today. 

</TEXT>

