<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Calls For Cooperation With Assemblies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602210294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1801 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 26 Feb (TANJUG) -- Bnanko Vojnica, speaker of 
the assembly of the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK], has sent, 
via the diplomatic and consular offices in Belgrade, a letter to 
representatives of all parliaments in the world calling on them 
to establish working contacts with Krajina's parliament. 
  Since your government does not recognize the RSK government 
and does not want to exchange information and engage in 
arguments with it, I suggest that our two parliaments establish 
working contacts and thus contribute to ending the war and the 
suffering of innocent people and to solving all disputes in the 
territory of the former Yugoslavia by peaceful means, the letter 
says. 
  Vojnica informs the parliaments about the history of the 
Serb 
people in the territory of former Croatia and stresses that the 
Serbs do not want to live in the same state with Croats. 
  The letter also quotes the results of the multiparty 
elections held in the RSK last December, and says that through 
the elections the people of the RSK confirmed their right to 
self-determination. 

</TEXT>

