<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Visits Karachi, Ankara </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602082594 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1830 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The government aircraft carrying Slovak Prime 
Minister Vladimir Meciar and his entourage made two stopovers on 
the way back from China so that our leaders could have more 
political talks. 
  During the stopover at the airport in Karachi in southern 
Pakistan, Vladimir Meciar was received by a minister authorized 
by Prime Minister Bhutto, who was on a foreign trip at the time. 
Apart from political and economic issues, they discussed 
cooperation in tourism. In this respect, the Pakistani side was 
interested in the conditions for foreign capital entry into our 
market. A government delegation and a group of businessmen will 
come to Slovakia and examine the potential and forms of possible 
capital investments in our country. 
  The government aircraft landed in Ankara after a four-hour 
flight from Karachi. Vladimir Meciar met Turkish Foreign 
Minister Hikmet Cetin there. Their conversation, which lasted 
approximately 30 minutes, focused, apart from political issues, 
on the problems of forming a Slovak-Turkish intergovernmental 
commission for economic cooperation. One of the other topics 
they discussed was a joint armaments program and the drafting of 
a plan on cooperation in the sphere of building oil and gas 
pipelines. The two sides also agreed that it was necessary to 
prepare a new cultural agreement. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

