<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Plans To Leave Politics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502203294 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1830 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1830 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference in Bratislava today, Slovak 
Minister of Foreign Affairs Jozef Moravcik reaffirmed his 
intention not to leave Slovak politics. Together with the group 
that, as a part of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia, 
supported the Alternative of Political Realism, he intends to 
form a strong bloc oriented at the center of the political 
spectrum. This group counts on Cernak's [National Democratic] 
wing of the Slovak National Party and on the Alliance of 
Democrats of the Slovak Republic. But talks with other parties 
are also in progress. 
  Asked how he sees frequent changes in the post of Slovak 
foreign minister, inasmuch as in other countries foreign 
ministers retain their posts regardless of changes in the 
composition of elected coalitions, Jozef Moravcik said: A 
mechanism allowing this practice to be implemented should be 
created in Slovakia. Slovak foreign policy does not benefit 
from frequent changes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

