<H3> <TI>   Croatian Army Blamed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802095694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 3d Corps report from Zenica] </F>
  [Excerpt] Much more is needed for peace than just 
signatures on a piece of paper, most of all it requires the 
goodwill of the commanders of military units on the ground. We 
do not want to believe that one thing is agreed at the 
negotiating table while another thing is told the military 
commanders, those who implement the cease-fire. However, how 
else can we explain the bombing of the Novi Travnik Bratstvo 
[Brotherhood] factory from aircraft of the Croatian Army, as 
happened this morning at 0648 [0548 GMT]? Is there any 
justification for daily overflights of helicopters of the 
Croatian Army over the Vitez region, which drop military 
hardware to the extremist units, as happened yesterday over 
Jardol and Nova Bila? [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

