<H3> <TI>   Eyewitnesses Confirm Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802113794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ahmed Begicevic from Novi Travnik] </F>
  [Text] Early this morning the citizens of Novi Travnik and 
Travnik were awoken by a series of powerful explosions. 
According to the information that we have received from the 
Operative Group Bosanska Krajina, this morning at 0645 [0545 
GMT] a group of six Galeb fighter planes bearing the insignia of 
the former Yugoslav People's Army entered the air space of our 
country despite the UN no-fly resolution. Four planes bombed 
the Bratstvo Factory in Novi Travnik, causing considerable 
material damage. 
  Just after this air raid NATO planes appeared in the sky, 
and 
the attackers dispersed and tried to escape in various 
directions. Early morning eye-witnesses in Travnik have 
confirmed that an armed clash took place in the sky, and the 
attackers were attacked by missiles from the NATO planes, which 
were much faster. According to unofficial information [words 
indistinct] two U.S. F-16 fighters. 

</TEXT>

