<F P=103> AU2802093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Atif Agic from Bugojno] </F>
  [Text] This morning at 0650 [0550 GMT] the chetnik air 
force again bombed residential areas in Bugojno. The air raid 
was carried out in three sweeps, causing great material damage. 
After dropping their load, the chetnik bombers flew off in the 
direction of Donji Vakuf. 
  Since 1745 last night the chetnik artillery has been 
pounding 
the residential areas of Bugojno, and this was repeated early 
this morning during the chetnik air raid. 
  All the defense lines of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
fighters 
from Operative Group West are firm and alert. 
  As for the Gornji Vakuf front, the cease-fire is largely 
holding, at least as far as the artillery is concerned. Snipers 
are still active, and something should be done about these 
criminals, as that is in the interest of both sides. 

