<F P=102>  AU2802121294 Paris AFP in English 1154 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, Feb 28 (AFP) -- UN soldiers cancelled the 
opening set for Monday [28 February] of a bridge linking the 
Serb and Moslem sides of divided Sarajevo, UN General Michael 
Rose told reporters. 
  The commander of UN forces in Bosnia said he had "an 
agreement in principle not in writing" with Bosnian Serb 
authorities and that he felt he needed a written agreement 
concerning the terms for opening the bridge. 

