<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `All-Out Attack' by Serbs in Central Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702114894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2702114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation in the free territories of Tesanj, 
Maglaj, Doboj, and Teslic is extremely serious. In fact, it is 
dramatic. Decisive battles are being waged. The enemy is 
pounding civilians and residential areas with unprecedented 
savagery. The 133-km long defense line of the Seven South 
Operative Group is in flames. The Serb aggressor has engaged 
almost 50 percent of their military might in Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
including heavy artillery withdrawn from the Sarajevo 
battlefield. This all-out attack, which the army of occupation 
calls Borders '94, is coordinated personally by war criminals 
generals Mladic and Talic. The aim is to establish the southern 
border of the phantom Serb state in the area of the Vranduk 
tunnel. The free territories of Tesanj, Maglaj, Doboj, and 
Teslic are -- believe it or not -- being hit by more than 200 
heavy shells every hour. These barbaric attacks aiming at 
systematic destruction of civilians and their homes have outdone 
everything seen so far on the territory of Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  As I am reporting, tank and howitzer shells are raining down 
onto the town of Tesanj, as was the case throughout last night. 
However, the situation is the most serious in Maglaj where most 
civilians are dying. Specifically, the army of occupation is 
doing its best to capture Maglaj and drive out its remaining 
surviving residents. We are reminding the international 
community once again, for the umpteenth time, that Maglaj and 
Tesanj have been encircled by the aggressor and completely 
sealed off for nine months. This is the only area in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina where the aggressor is stopping all convoys 
with food and other goods for civilians. 
  However, our soldiers have not given in. In hand to hand 
fighting, the joint units of the Seven South Operative Group and 
the 2d Corps of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army have halted the 
aggressor, and everyone is determined to die rather than allow 
the army of occupation to enter Tesanj and Maglaj. All defense 
lines are unchanged, and the aggressor is suffering heavy, truly 
heavy, losses in manpower. Our soldiers keep on fighting. 
Hajrudin Rezovic reported from the information center of the 
Seven South Operative Group. 

</TEXT>

