<F P=102>  LD2602091294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0700 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency Alija 
Izetbegovic sent a letter yesterday [25 February] to the UN 
Security Council. The letter says: 
  A ferocious offensive on Maglaj has been going on for days 
now. The situation is deteriorating by the hour due to the 
employment of the heavy artillery the Serb aggressor withdrew 
from around Sarajevo. The Bosnia-Herzegovina Army has done and 
is doing everything it possibly can to rescue the town and its 
residents. Our defenses are flagging due to the enemy's 
technical superiority. Thousands of civilians -- mostly women 
and children -- are facing a fresh massacre. We are demanding 
urgent action on the part of the United Nations to forestall 
genocide, President Izetbegovic's letter says. 

