<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, the president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, has sent a letter to Palestinian 
President Yasir 'Arafat in connection with the massacre of 
Palestinians in the town of Hebron. 
  The letter reads: I am shocked by the news of the horrific 
massacre of Palestinians in Hebron. The seriousness of the 
incident is aggravated by the fact that it took place during the 
holy month of Ramadan, in God's shrine, during the holy act of 
morning prayer. The latest crime in Hebron, like the recent 
massacre at the market in Sarajevo, is the kind of crime that 
leaves one speechless. We consider the innocent victims at the 
mosque in Hebron to be our own. We pray God to bestow 
everlasting blessings upon the dead and give patience to their 
families, the letter says. 

