<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Koljevic Discusses Political Integration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602160694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2602160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Excerpt" from an interview with Nikola Koljevic, vice </F>
president of the Srpska republic, by an unidentified 
correspondent on 26 February; from the "Sa Lica Mesta" program 
-- recorded] 
  [Text] [Koljevic] In short, we believe that the Russian 
initiative is very good, that superpowers and big nations should 
participate, and that their authority -- political and any other 
-- will grow further. Therefore, in principle the Russian plan 
involves greater authority and thus also a quicker solution. We 
shall see who is pleased with this initiative and who is not. 
For the time being the replies from the West have been a bit 
reserved and ambiguous. However, we support such an initiative 
in any case. Regarding the U.S. plan, if we demand 
self-determination for ourselves and know that the Serbian side 
would not agree to any sort of political dependence or 
subordination to other sides, we have no democratic right, and 
we must allow the negotiations between the Muslims and the 
Croats, especially in the political sphere, as long as they are 
not to our detriment. These talks have to do with an internal 
matter, a question of their domestic relations, so to speak; 
naturally, this is all based on the fundamental assumption that 
this will not be a military alliance, as it was at the beginning 
of the war, but a political integration that suits them. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Given the circumstances, how 
should one understand the position of the Serbs and define the 
Serbian interest? 
  [Koljevic] Well, I believe that this was already defined a 
few days ago -- in THE WASHINGTON POST yesterday or the day 
before -- namely, that the Serbs will be absolutely free to 
choose their form of constitution, that they will be able to set 
themselves up independently in the Srpska republic or unify with 
Serbia, which is actually the wish of the people and in our 
natural historic interest. This is already being mentioned 
publicly as a viable option in the United States if this thing 
between the Muslims and the Croats proves to be viable. 

</TEXT>

