<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Ante Rose, chief of staff of the Croatian 
Defense Council [HVO], has lodged a protest note with General 
Jean Cot, UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] commander for the area 
of the former Yugoslavia, and General Michael Rose, UN peace 
force commander in Bosnia-Herzegovina, following cease-fire 
violations by the Bosnia-Herzegovina army. In his letter General 
Roso states that Muslim forces launched a heavy attack today on 
the free territory of Zepce, using mortars and howitzers. One 
HVO soldier was killed and three wounded in these attacks. 
  In his letter General Roso says that Muslim forces organized 
and staged an HVO attack on their positions on the eastern side 
of Mostar. They had in advance positioned TV cameramen who were 
supposed to film this artillery action, thus gaining a certain 
political as well as military advantage. General Roso demands 
that UNPROFOR take measures on the ground in order to thwart 
similar action. 

