<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Protests Muslim Trench-Building </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602224094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2134 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602224094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 26 Feb (TANJUG) -- Radovan Karadzic, 
president of the Srpska republic [RS], this evening warned the 
UN Secretary General's special envoy, Yasushi Akashi, that 
Muslim forces are abusing the Sarajevo cease-fire in order to 
gain a military advantage. 
  In a letter to Akashi, a copy of which has been sent to 
TANJUG, Karadzic points out that since the first day of the 
cease-fire Muslim forces have been moving their trench lines 
towards Serb positions. 
  "These engineering works have been going on constantly, 
right 
up to today," Karadzic alleges, assessing that this is "an 
attempt to improve their military position under cover of the 
cease-fire." 
  The RS president points out that these Muslim cease-fire 
violations are being carried out in many places -- in Mojmilo 
(three or four places), in the Jewish cemetery, in the 
Dobrinja-Vojkovici area (two places), Rajlovac (three places), 
on Zuc (two places), in Brijesce and in the Butmir-Ilidza area. 
  "We strongly protest against these Muslim military 
activities, which are a clear and flagrant violation of the 
Serb-Muslim agreement reached on 9 February," Karadzic writes, 
assessing that "this cease-fire which was realized with such 
difficulty is now under serious threat." 
  "Furthermore, the whole peace process is now in danger. 
Unless the newly dug Muslim trenches are abandoned and 
destroyed, the already begun measures to build confidence will 
suffer huge damage," Karadzic assesses, adding that "if 
something is not done quickly," the Serb side will not be able 
to continue its cooperation in the efforts to achieve peace in 
the Sarajevo region. 

</TEXT>

