<H3> <TI>   Presidency Announces Reorganization of Army </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602215594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The presidency of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina held a session today, chaired by President of 
the Presidency Alija Izetbegovic. 
  The presidency passed a decision on changes in the 
territorial organization of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army: A new, 
7th Corps of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army has been set up, and 
the 6th Corps has been abolished, or rather, merged with the 4th 
Corps [operating in the Mostar area]. Brigadier Mehmed Alagic, 
former commander of the 3d Corps [operating in the Zenica area] 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, has been appointed commander of 
the 7th Corps. Brigadier Sahib Mahmudin, former chief of staff 
of the 3d Corps of the Bosnia- Herzegovina Army, has been 
appointed commander of the 3d Corps of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Army. 
  The presidency accepted the resignation of Mufid Memija from 
the post of director general of Sarajevo Radio-Television. 
Amila Omerpasic, electrical engineer, has been appointed acting 
director general. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

