<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Luczak Discusses Cooperation With ROK Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502152694 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1341 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 25 Feb--Deputy Prime Minister Aleksander 
Luczak received today Pang Yong-toc, ambassador of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea. Views were exchanged on 
possibilities for intensifying contacts between both countries, 
the government press office reports. 
  The ambassador emphasized that his country pursued its own 
political path, but wanted to maintain good relations with all 
states that respected this choice. He underscored that he hoped 
new cooperation with Poland in the scientific and technological 
field is established soon. He pointed out that an enlivening of 
contacts between health services of both countries would be 
desirable, as well as the signing of an agreement on mutual 
recognition of medical degrees. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Luczak expressed the view that 
different political systems did not have to make good bilateral 
relations impossible. He acknowledged that an expansion of 
trade cooperation would be beneficial to both countries. 
  Both sides agreed to the need for the resumption of 
exchanges 
of students, which was stopped some years ago, the communique 
says. 

</TEXT>

