<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   SLD: Agreement on Deputy Minister Reached </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2802113594 Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA in Polish 26-27 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> WS2802113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw RZECZPOSPOLITA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Z.L.: "There Is Agreement Concerning Defense"] </F>
  [Text] The future "coalition" deputy minister of national 
defense will be responsible for contacts with the Sejm. The 
decision on establishing the post of "the parliamentary 
undersecretary of state" in the Ministry of National Defense 
[MON] was made during the talks with the participation of 
Minister Piotr Kolodziejczyk. Jerzy Milewski, National Security 
Office head and secretary of state in MON, did not take part in 
the last stage of the negotiations. The first deputy of the 
national defense minister has been in the hospital for a week 
now. "The possibility cannot be ruled out that the personnel 
decisions will be made as early as next Monday [28 February)," 
Colonel Wieslaw Rozbicki, MON spokesman, informed on 25 
February. Jerzy Szmajdzinski, general secretary of the Social 
Democracy of the Polish Republic, Sejm deputy of the Democratic 
Left Alliance, and chairman of the Sejm Defense Committee, 
confirmed on 25 February that the agreement on the filling of 
the post of the "political" deputy minister had been reached 
with the MON leadership. In line with the procedures, the 
candidate for the deputy minister should be proposed to the 
prime minister by the minister. "There already exists a list of 
candidates for the portfolio of the deputy minister," said 
Szmajdzinski; he firmly denied that his name is on that list. 
"The Government Press Office is not in the habit of acting 
before things actually happen. We issue information about 
recalls and appointments that have actually been made in the 
government," we heard on 25 February in the Office of the 
Council of Ministers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-7794 </DOCNO>
