<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Speaker on Security, Army Finances </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2802105794 Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network in 
Polish 0635 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2802105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Polish Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy; place and </F>
date not given; from the "Caliber" Military Program--recorded] 
  [Text] Speaking in terms of strategic perspective, my view 
is that Poland is not safe, and everyone should become aware of 
that fact soon, and also implement the necessary measures in 
order to increase the feeling of safety. Second, there is the 
issue of financial means for the very urgent needs of the Army, 
in order to secure the Army's efficiency and 
effectiveness--there have been debates going on regarding that 
issue for some time now. The state budget presents an 
opportunity in that regard. I think that if additional revenues 
for the state budget emerge this year--there are people hoping 
that this will happen--then the Army's needs must definitely be 
taken into account. Third, I also think that there is no social 
awareness of the deteriorating security in the country and the 
resultant need to strengthen the Army's role so that the role 
can be played well in the future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

