<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zieleniec Returns From Visit to Switzerland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502215094 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1700 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502215094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Czech Foreign Minister Josef Zieleniec today 
returned from a two-day visit of Switzerland, where he had talks 
with his counterpart, Flavio Cotti, and with the president of 
the Swiss Confederation, Otto Stich. He had this to say, among 
other things, about the outcome of his trip: 
  [Begin Zieleniec recording] The character of the visit was 
primarily to put a seal on the present level of relations 
between our two countries. We have also signed mutual letters, 
in which we have confirmed the validity of obligations both 
countries have against each other in international law. 
Moreover, Switzerland is our important trade partner. Despite 
its being such a small country, it occupies 12th position in our 
trade relations with the outside world, which is very 
remarkable. It was therefore natural that we should have also 
discussed matters concerning the expansion of trade and economic 
cooperation. Swiss companies are participating with distinction 
in the process of the transformation of the economy. I have, 
however, also noted that the first swallows of our capital 
expansion, if I may say so, have appeared in Switzerland. Some 
of our companies have already set up mixed companies or branches 
directly in Switzerland. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

