<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Supports NATO Air Force Action </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802144894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman, who is on a 
two-day official visit to Albania, after the talks with his host 
Albanian President Sali Berisha expressed support for the NATO 
air force action today against the Serb planes, which had been 
violating the UN resolution on the no-fly zone over 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  He described it is a sign of resoluteness by the 
international community to oppose Serb aggression and Russian 
interference in the Balkans. We completely agree with 
international factors, the United States, the EU, and NATO 
showing greater resolve in suppressing aggression. We interpret 
this as a signal that the international community will continue 
to take resolute steps to end the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and create preconditions for peace, the Croatian president said. 
  In reply to Albanian journalists' questions, the Croatian 
president said NATO's latest move also demonstrated the 
resoluteness of the world's greatest super-power, the United 
States, to oppose Russian interference in the Balkans. As I 
have already said, I see this as a display of the resolve of the 
main European countries and the biggest world super-power, the 
United States, to oppose the Serb aggression, and, I would also 
say, Russian interference in the Balkans, Tudjman replied. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

