<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Kovac Attends MKDH Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602144594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hungarian Christian Democratic Movement [MKDH] 
republican assembly opened in Dunajska Streda this morning. It 
is attended by President Michal Kovac, who, in his greeting 
address, emphasized the importance of Hungarian political 
parties on our present political scene and said that 
difficulties arising in connection with minorities should be 
solved on the basis of civic principles. Equality of all 
citizens is the prime and basic cornerstone of democratic states 
and must not be questioned. 
  The speech by MKDH Chairman Vojtech Bugar analyzed the 
current political scene and emphasized that the MKDH considered 
that one of the most important tasks is to implement 
[Slovakia's] administrative and territorial division and to 
speed up putting self-administration in the sphere of education 
and culture on a legal basis. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

