<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Fighters Down Four Serbian Planes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802101494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0952 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rome, 28 February (TANJUG) -- It has been confirmed 
in the American Air Force base in Aviano in northeastern Italy 
that two American F-16 fighters from this base downed four 
planes this morning at 0530, 55 miles east of Banja Luka. U.S. 
fighter planes that returned to the base at around 0600 fired 
six "air-to-air" missiles at a group of six planes, sources in 
Aviano said. 
  The identity of the downed planes has not been officially 
confirmed yet, but it is presumed that they are Galeb planes 
belonging to the Serb republic air force. 

</TEXT>

