<H3> <TI>   Milosevic Hails Russian Involvement in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802190294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1832 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 28 Feb (TANJUG) -- Republic of Serbia 
President Slobodan Milosevic this evening received Gennadiy 
Shikin, Russian Federation ambassador in Belgrade, who handed 
him a letter from Russian President Boris Yeltsin. The letter 
deals with Russia's involvement, initiatives and role, as well 
as its efforts in solving the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  Russia's involvement and its efforts to solve the crisis in 
the framework of the peace process is, President Milosevic 
believes, of great importance and can make a decisive 
contribution to reaching a lasting and just peace in former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, a statement from the office of the president 
of the Republic of Serbia says. 

