<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Oil Field Commences Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103105894 Belgrade POLITIKA in Serbo-Croatian 26 Feb 94 p 
7 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade POLITIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Dj.B. and M.P.: "The Richest Oil Field in </F>
Serbia"] 
  [Text] Turija, 25 Feb -- Today's launching of regular 
production in the first phase of the "Turija North 1" oil field 
in the vicinity of Srbobran marks the 45th anniversary of the 
Serbian oil company "Naftagas." 
  The "Turija North 1" oil field is the largest of its kind 
discovered in Serbia over the past three decades. According to 
"Naftagas" manager Srboljub Stankovic, Turija and the eastern 
part of Srbobran literally stand on oil. The subterranean field, 
situated between two points at a depth of 2,000 meters is coated 
in a layer of oil 47 meters thick. 
  Some $60 million has so far been invested in the "Turija 
North 1" oil field. This year, another $32 million is needed 
for the second phase of construction, while the third phase -- 
the construction of transportation systems and oil and gas 
pipelines calls for another $11 million. 
  Around 86,000 metric tons of oil were produced in this area 
last year. This year, the production of 120,000 tons of oil is 
planned. 
  Vladimir Zivanovic, republican minister for energy, was 
among 
the many guests who attended today's celebrations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

