<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Army Deploying Tanks, Artillery </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802200994 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Reports from Prishtina confirm that the Serbian 
Army continues its movements throughout Kosova. Some 200 
Serbian soldiers, tanks, and other heavy artillery have been 
deployed in Kacanik city. Near Kacanik, at Hani i Elezit, a 
border point between Kosova and FYROM [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia], the Serbian army killed another Albanian 
today -- 60-year-old Selman Pajazit Daci. 
  The Kosova Information Center reports that Selman Daci was 
killed by the Serbian soldiers on the Prishtina-Skopje road. 
Other details have not been announced so far. 
  There are reports of concentrations of the Serbian forces at 
a place called Cuka e Komoranit, near Gllogovc. A total of 13 
tanks, dozens of military trucks, and other heavy artillery have 
been stationed there. 

</TEXT>

