<H3> <TI>   Demirel Repeats Readiness To Aid Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802200794 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Gligorov's Message to Demirel"] </F>
  [Text] The President of the Republic of Turkey Suleyman 
Demirel received in Ankara the Macedonian Ambassador Trajan 
Petrovski. The latter delivered a message from the Macedonian 
President Kiro Gligorov and informed Mr. Demirel on Macedonian 
economic losses due to the latest embargo imposed by a Greek 
Government decision. 
  President Demirel repeated Turkey's readiness to aid 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
in its efforts to cope with difficulties. 

</TEXT>

