<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gligorov Denies Territorial Aspirations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802200694 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Macedonia Keeps Its Name"] </F>
  [Text] At the large gathering in Kumanovo, on the occasion 
of the 50th anniversary of forming of the Third Macedonian 
Brigade, President Gligorov stated among other things: "We are 
very much interested in building friendly relations and 
cooperation with all our neighbors, based on neighborly 
cooperation and in the interest of the peace and stability in 
the region. That permanent determination of ours can not be 
threatened by various blockades, political and economic 
pressures, like the recent decision of the Greek Government to 
close its border and its Thessalonike port for our goods. Just 
like before, we firmly stand up to all pressures and will not 
allow any one to deny us the name we have had with centuries. 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
survives and will go on surviving. We have no territorial 
aspirations towards any of our neighbors, and therefore not 
towards our southern one, either. That is why we propose, with 
a clear conscience, to sit down and discuss all the differences 
between our two countries, on an equal basis." 

</TEXT>

