<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR, RSK To Control Bridge </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2702162094 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1600 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2702162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jovan Vlajkovic] </F>
  [Text] As of 0800 tomorrow, one soldier of the Serbian 
army of Krajina and one member of the ministry of internal 
affairs of the republic of Serbian Krajina [RSK] together with 
the members of the Nepalese Battalion of the UN Protection 
Forces [UNPROFOR] will control the crossing of the RSK state 
border on the Bridge of Serbian Unity. 
  This is a result of an agreement between [UNPROFOR] General 
Jean Cot and General Milan Celeketic, reached today on the 
bridge itself. They also discussed other similar locations in 
the RSK; however, the details were left to future negotiations. 
  According to General Jean Cot, the entire situation 
concerning the bridge should not have reached the dimensions it 
did. All future disputes will be resolved through talks. It is 
not the first time that I have talked with General Celeketic. 
Knowing him, I am sure that all misunderstandings will be 
resolved through negotiation. 

</TEXT>

