<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha Condemns Serb Closure of Academy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602211494 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2602211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The president of the Republic's spokesman reports 
that President Sali Berisha harshly condemned the decision and 
considered criminal and barbarous the final act of the Serbian 
Government against the Academy of Sciences and Arts of the 
Republic of Kosova. This is an unprecedented escalation in the 
history of present civilization and in the fight against 
science, culture, and truth. 
  With this the Serbian regime testifies once more to its 
determination to fanatically implement the criminal memorandum 
of the Academy of Sciences which, drafted on principles of 
anticivilization and barbarism, sets forth the notions of ethnic 
cleansing and the erasure of thinking in other nations. 
  The Serbian circles can close a building, but they can by no 
means suffocate the thinking and scientific truth of the 
Albanian world. The act is as antiscientific and illegitimate 
as it is barbarous. 

</TEXT>

