<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slovenia's Peterle Visits, Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Iliescu, Vacaroiu </H4>
<F P=102> AU0103070894 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
2000 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103070894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Slovene Foreign Minister Lojze Peterle concluded 
his visit to Bucharest tonight. The program of his visit 
included a meeting with Romanian President Ion Iliescu at 
Cotroceni Palace. 
  According to statements made by the guest to our 
correspondent, during the meeting aspects and common aspects of 
the transition process in both countries and issues referring to 
security and bilateral relations were discussed. 
  Mr. Lojze Peterle was also received by Prime Minister 
Nicolae 
Vacaroiu. The meeting was also attended by Romanian Foreign 
Minister Teodor Melescanu. During the meeting the sides 
assessed the stage of relations between the two countries in the 
regional, European, and world context. The sides also briefed 
each other about the development of the process of transition to 
market economy. The dialogue provided a good opportunity for 
the sides to emphasize the possibility of furthering and 
expanding relations between Romania and Slovenia on the basis of 
the summit meetings that are going to be held and of the 
bilateral accords that will be signed in the near future. 
  Mr. Lojze Peterle also held talks with Romanian Foreign 
Minister Teodor Melescanu. An accord between the government of 
the two countries on cooperation in the areas of education, 
culture, science, and sports as well as the protocol on 
cooperation between the two ministries were signed. 
  The guest was also received by Adrian Nastase, chairman of 
the Chamber of Deputies of the Romanian parliament. 

</TEXT>

