<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Troops Using Tunnel Under Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602145494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1309 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2602145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 26 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Moslems late last 
week transported around two thousand of their soldiers to the 
battlefronts in central Bosnia through a tunnel under Sarajevo, 
the Czech daily LIDOVE NOVINI writes on Saturday. 
  The daily's special reporter quotes a British U.N. 
Protection 
Force (UNPROFOR) officer, who asked not to be identified as 
saying that the Moslems have connected a tunnel under the 
Sarajevo airport in the southern section of the city with 
another in northern Sarajevo, whose locality as yet remains 
unknown. 
  Following a meeting with the UNPROFOR command, the same 
source said, the Moslem side agreed to place both tunnels under 
UNPROFOR's "discreet control," the daily says. 
  Bosnian Serbs several months ago warned that the Moslems had 
dug a tunnel under the UNPROFOR-controlled Sarajevo airport to 
be used as a conduit for arms and ammunition deliveries and 
transportation of troops. 
  However, Bosnian Serbs and Croats have for the past few days 
been stressing that the Moslem side has taken advantage of the 
Serb-Moslem ceasefire in the Sarajevo area to evacuate its 
troops and have them transferred to central Bosnia to help step 
up an offensive against Bosnian Croats. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

