<H3> <TI>   Karadzic To Discuss Peace Process in Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802211694 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2802211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Radovan Karadzic, president of the Srpska </F>
republic, by Zeljko Avramovic at an unidentified airport on 28 
February -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Avramovic] Mr. Karadzic, you are leaving for 
Moscow to pay the first official visit after the triumphal 
return of Russian diplomacy to the world political scene. What 
aim does this visit have? 
  [Karadzic] This is an invitation, an official invitation to 
our delegation to come to have talks mostly about the peace 
process and the first visit will certainly pass mostly in 
further examining the possibilities of reaching peace; both 
peace in general and the one around Sarajevo, possibly around 
Tuzla regarding the opening of the airport, and so on. In a 
word, Russia is now much more present both in a diplomatic and a 
military sense and we are very pleased to be going to Russia. 
  [Avramovic] Whom are you going to meet in Moscow? 
  [Karadzic] Our hosts are Churkin and Kozyrev. We are 
certainly going to meet them and we shall see about the rest. 
So far, we do not know the plan. 

</TEXT>

