<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Srpska Republic Joins FRY Financial System </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802151894 Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio in Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pale Srpski Radio-Televizija Studio Sarajevo 
Radio </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Srpska republic is as of today a part of the 
unified financial system of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia 
[FRY], Vladimir Lukic, the Srpska prime minister, said after a 
meeting in Banja Luka with representatives of banks, the chamber 
of the economy, the customs administration, the economic 
institute, and large companies in the republic. 
  The Srpska republic's government has adopted all regulations 
from the program of financial reconstruction and economic 
recovery of Yugoslavia, Lukic said. He added that now it is only 
a matter of technical details as to when the new dinar would 
appear and become the only means of payment in the Srpska 
republic. 

</TEXT>

