<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on `Act of Terror' in Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802211494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1900 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Polish Ministry of Foreign Affairs [MSZ] is 
deeply concerned about the serious increase in tension in the 
Middle East. At the same time, the MSZ expresses its profound 
condemnation of the act of terror that took place at the Hebron 
mosque, a statement issued by the Ministry says. According to 
the Polish MSZ, this tragic incident and its consequences have 
harmed the atmosphere of the peace process in the Middle East 
and are threatening to undermine the results achieved so far. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-7871 </DOCNO>
