<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ends Visit; Cooperation Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402112094 Prague CTK in English 1004 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2402112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava Feb 24 (CTK) -- Yevgeniy Primakov, chief 
of the Russian Intelligence Service, today ended his visit to 
Slovakia and left for Vienna. 
  In Bratislava, he held talks with the Slovak Information 
Service and met with President Michal Kovac, Parliament Deputy 
Chairman Augustin Marian Huska and Deputy Premier Jozef Prokes. 
  According to official sources, cooperation between the two 
countries' information services will concentrate on fighting 
international crime, terrorism, trade in drugs and weapons as 
well as on exchange of information on sites of war in Europe. 
The two services have also agreed to exchange their liaison 
officers in Moscow and Bratislava. 

</TEXT>

