<H3> <TI>   Science Academy Condemns Serb Action in Kosovo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602184194 Tirana ATA in English 0927 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2602184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 26 (ATA) -- The Albanian Academy 
of Sciences condemned today, through a statement, the illegal 
and anti-scientific act of the Serbian invading authorities in 
Kosova who confiscated on February 23 the building of the Kosova 
Academy of Sciences and Arts in Prishtina. The Academy of 
Sciences of Albania regards the Serbian act as part of a 
short-sighted policy inspired by a medieval mentality. 
  The Albania's Science Academy appeals to all the world 
academies and the progressive international community to protest 
against those illegal acts in order that the Albanian scientists 
in the Republic of Kosova may freely exercise their peaceful 
activity serving the science and prosperity. 

</TEXT>

