<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Hints at Territorial Claims in FYROM </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402130294 Sofia BTA in English 1106 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2402130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From BTA press review] </F>
  [Excerpts] Sofia, February 24 (BTA) -- [passage omitted] 
During a visit of BSP [Bulgarian Socialist Party] MP's to Serbia 
two weeks ago, Miroslav Durmov MP of the BSP proposed that the 
General Staffs of Bulgaria and Serbia draft a document for 
military control and confidence, 24 CHASA reports today. 
According to Mr. Durmov such a document is vital as Serbia has 
not signed the Treaty on Conventional Armed Forces in Europe. 
Belgrade showed readiness to start immediate discussion of 
confidence building measures, Gen. Miodrag Terzic of Serbia's 
Defence Ministry said, quoted by the daily. [passage omitted] 
  Within a year at the latest Bulgaria could lay territory 
claims to the present state of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], demanding first official 
protection for the Bulgarian population there, NOVINAR says 
today, quoting a high-ranking diplomat of the Foreign Ministry 
in Sofia. This dramatic reversal of Bulgaria's position towards 
Macedonia would be a consequence of Russia's increased activity 
in the Balkans, the paper adds. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

