<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zieleniec, Poland's Oleksy Discuss Europe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802171494 Prague CTK in English 1656 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Feb 28 (CTK) -- Czech Foreign Minister Josef 
Zieleniec met with Speaker of the Polish Sejm (parliament) Jozef 
Oleksy on Monday [28 February] to discuss the questions of 
European security, integration into the European structures and 
the course of transformation in the Czech Republic and Poland. 
Oleksy has been on a three-day visit to the Czech Republic 
since Sunday [27 February]. 
  The two politicians expressed satisfaction over good 
relations between Poland and the Czech Republic. Oleksy showed 
interest in the Czech Republic's efforts at integrating in 
Europe and in its opinion of the NATO Partnership for Peace 
initiative as well as on its relation to NATO and the European 
Union. 
  Zieleniec voiced the view that countries attempting at 
joining these institutions should first become fully ready. 
  The two countries' relations toward Russia and Ukraine and 
the possibility for these countries' participation in European 
structures and the future European security system were also 
discussed. Zieleniec and Oleksy also paid attention to the 
regional cooperation which embraces, along with cultural and 
economic relations, also cooperation in some political problems. 

</TEXT>

