<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel Receives Sejm Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802202394 Prague CTK in English 1838 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lany, Central Bohemia Feb 28 (CTK) -- Technical and 
administrative aspects of the integration of the Czech Republic 
and Poland into the European Union were discussed on Monday [28 
February] by Czech President Vaclav Havel and Speaker of the 
Polish Sejm (parliament) Jozef Oleksy, Oleksy told journalists. 
Oleksy said he spoke with Havel about pan-European matters, 
while he discussed more concrete concerns with other Czech 
representatives. 
  The talks dealt generally with the European situation and 
integration, the Polish Constitution which is in preparation, 
the role of the president and the balance of power in the 
political system, Havel's spokesman Ladislav Spacek said. 

</TEXT>

