<F P=102>  AU2802173694 Budapest MTI in English 1539 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 28 Feb (MTI) -- The Hungarian Interior 
Ministry does not plan to take any special measures along the 
country's southern border, Interior Minister Imre Konya told the 
press in Budapest today. The announcement came after the 
shooting of four aircraft in Bosnia at Monday dawn. 
Nevertheless, plans are available for coping with emergencies, 
the minister said. 

