<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iliescu Condemns `Irresponsible Act' in Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602165194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1526 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2602165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES 26/2/1994 -- Romania's President 
Ion Iliescu has sent a telegram of condolence to Yasir `Arafat, 
president of the state of Palestine, president of the Executive 
Committee of the PLO, in which he firmly condemns "the criminal 
and irresponsible act committed in Hebron, Cisjordan." 
  "We express our conviction that the Palestinian people and 
the PLO leadership would know how to overcome this sad and 
dramatic moment of hard trial and sufferings, honouring the 
memory of the Palestinian martyrs in Hebron by new efforts and 
active demarches to further the process of peace in the Middle 
East," the telegram reads. 

</TEXT>

