<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vacaroiu on Possibility of Government Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802124894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1018 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Quotation marks as received] </F>
  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 28/2/1994 -- In an interview 
with daily COTIDIANUL, Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu 
said with reference to the previous statements on the 
possibility of making up a new government by March 1, 1994, that 
"the political dialogue continues. The final decision on a 
possible government reshuffle will depend also on these 
demarches that result from the political dialogue but, first, it 
will depend on the decision to make or not make a reshuffle and 
on establishing the persons to replace the present dignitaries. 
As long as I am the prime minister I am not starting from the 
idea of a reshuffle for the sake of reshuffle." 
  Referring to the government's reform program, he said that 
"the strategy we have articulated, including the program of 
measures and actions for 1994 has an anti-crisis character. It 
has nothing new, actually stemming from the government's 
strategy. "Sure," he added, "it is a program of the (ruling) 
party of Social Democracy of Romania, on which all ministries 
worked, especially that most ministers are members of this 
party. Besides, the problem of a dialogue was posed and this 
seems very fair to me, with the parties that backed the 
government in 1993, concerning a string of objectives included 
in this program. The outlook differs in some respects. 
However, there is a point that unites us and on which we can 
agree, I mean especially the social protection." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

