<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Welcomes Bosnia Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203130594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0203130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a communique issued today the Romanian Ministry 
of Foreign Affairs states that it has noted with satisfaction 
the fact that -- with the considerable contribution of the U.S. 
Administration -- an accord was concluded on the establishment 
of a Croatian-Muslim federation in Bosnia-Herzegovina and a 
confederation between the latter and Croatia. 
  Romania's Ministry of Foreign Affairs considers that the 
implementation of the stipulations of the aforementioned accord 
represents a substantial step toward the political settlement of 
the crisis in Bosnia-Herzegovina, parallel to efforts made to 
find solutions for the rest of the package of issues that is 
being negotiated. 
  Romania's Ministry of Foreign Affairs expresses the hope 
that 
this favorable moment will be turned to good account to the 
benefit of all parties and stability and security in the region, 
the communique concludes. 

</TEXT>

