<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Observers Note Violations in Moldovan Ballot </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203130794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0203130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The [Romanian] League for the Protection of Human 
Rights [LADO] and the Civic Alliance [AC] -- the organizations 
that sent groups of observers to monitor the [27 February] 
parliamentary elections in the Republic of Moldova -- found a 
number of violations of the electoral law, which they presented 
yesterday during a news conference held in Bucharest. 
  From among those irregularities, the list of which has been 
faxed to us, we mention the following: the broadcasting, on the 
eve of elections, of two speeches made by President Mircea 
Snegur, as the speeches doubtlessly had an electoral character; 
a number of cases in which votes were cast while more than one 
person was present in the ballot booths; a number of cases when 
votes were cast outside ballot booths; attempts made at certain 
polling stations to influence the voters; and the nonregistering 
of persons who had already voted, which allowed for the same 
persons to cast two or even more votes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

