<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Welcomes Croat-Muslim Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203085194 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
0800 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203085194 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Hungarian Foreign Minister] Geza Jeszenszky has 
said that Hungary sincerely supports the Croatian-Muslim 
reconciliation because these two nations are dependent on each 
other more than other countries of the region. The Hungarian 
foreign minister, who is currently holding talks in Washington, 
is of the opinion that, if the canton system enabling the 
coexistence of Croats and Muslims comes into prominence again in 
the case of Bosnia, the example, in a wider sense, will probably 
be followed elsewhere as well. 

</TEXT>

