<H3> <TI>   Mostar Radio Identifies Pilot </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103161994 Mostar Croatian Radio Herzeg-Bosna in 
Serbo-Croatian 1500 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mostar Croatian Radio Herzeg-Bosna </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dino Ramovic from Podgorica] </F>
  [Text] There is probably no more doubt left about the 
owners of Jastreb aircraft, downed by NATO planes above Bugojno 
yesterday. Zvjezdan Pesic, 31, was one of the pilots of the 
downed planes. His family in Podgorica was informed about this 
tragic event by the information service of the Yugoslav Army. 
According to the newly established independent Montenegrin news 
agency, MONTENA, Pesic's family has been living in Podgorica 
since last summer. They came here as refugees from Mostar. 
Pilot Zvjezdan Pesic was taken to the so-called Serb Republic 
in the course of a recent forceful mobilization. His death has 
been talked about in Podgorica since last night and many presume 
that some of the downed Jastreb planes had taken off from 
Podgorica airport. 

</TEXT>

