<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Objects to Proposal for Tuzla Airport </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103192394 Mainz ZDF Television Network in German 1800 GMT 
1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mainz ZDF Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Martin Schmuck] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] If Moscow and Bosnian Serb 
leader Karadzic have their way, the airport in Tuzla, an 
industrial town in eastern Bosnia, is to be opened and guarded 
by Russian blue-helmet soldiers. 
  Talking to ZDF, Bosnian Vice President Ejup Ganic said that 
this is unacceptable. Bosnia has more Russians than it needs. 
The country does not want any Russians, who do not cooperate in 
stopping the war. They are only supporting the Serbs and just 
serve to cover up the domestic problems between the government 
in Moscow and Russian right-wing extremist Zhirinovskiy and 
divert attention from their internal problems, Ganic stated. 

</TEXT>

