<H3> <TI>   ICRC Oversees Muslim-Croat Prisoner Exchange </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103200694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An exchange of Croatian and Bosnian prisoners was 
carried out in Bosnia-Herzegovina today under the auspices of 
the International Committee of the Red Cross [ICRC], the 
headquarters of this organization in Zagreb has reported. 
  The Bosnia-Herzegovina authorities released 61 Croats from a 
prison in Jablanica, while the Bosnian Croats released 128 
Bosniaks from Rodoc. 
  The prisoners will be transported to a destination of their 
choice. 
  At the same time, 200 Bosnian Croats left Jablanica with the 
help of the Red Cross. The majority of them were women and 
children. 

</TEXT>

