<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Bring Legal Action Over License </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203121194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1000 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Lech Walesa has said that he would bring 
legal action against the granting of the national television 
license to PolSat. Before leaving for India this morning, Lech 
Walesa said that one of the reasons behind the dismissal of 
Marek Markiewicz from the post of chairman of the National Radio 
and Television Broadcasting Council was the public signing of 
the license for PolSat. The president said that he would 
appoint a new chairman of the Council after his return from 
India next week. Lech Walesa added that, despite the dismissal 
of Markiewicz, the Council should carry on working as usual. 

</TEXT>

