<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Assembly Concludes First Plenary Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103205294 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by TANJUG correspondent Savo Jankovic from Knin] </F>
  [Text] The first plenary session of the first regular 
meeting of the assembly of the republic of Serbian Krajina [RSK] 
concluded this afternoon by electing members of seven 
parliamentary committees. The unanimous election of the 
commission members was preceded by the consultations held by the 
heads of caucuses, where a complete coordination was reached 
about the (?composition) of the committees, something that 
Assembly Chairman Branko (Vodnjica) stated with pleasure at the 
beginning of the afternoon part of the session. Immediately 
after the assembly committees were constituted, the first 
constitutive sessions of some of them were held while the 
remaining committees will do that by tomorrow morning. 
  The second plenary session is expected in the afternoon, 
which will most probably discuss the Krajina negotiatory 
platform in the peace process, amendments to which were 
initiated by President Milan Martic. By the way, at the morning 
part of the session today, Martic presented a report on the 
current political and security situation in Krajina. One may 
expect the plenary session [tomorrow] to discuss Martic's speech 
and there is also the possibility of the government submitting 
its report on the same topic. Moreover, the government is 
expected to submit a proposal on legal documents or ordinances 
regarding Krajina joining the united balance of payments with 
the FRY [Federal Republic of Yugoslavia], monetary 
reconstruction, and economic recovery. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

