<H3> <TI>   Choice of New FRY Envoy in Zagreb Attacked </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20438A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20438A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] The 14 February issue of the Split daily 
SLOBODNA DALMACIJA, in an article entitled "The Return of 
Comrade Veljko" on page 5, criticizes the appointment of Veljko 
Knezevic as head of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia [FRY] 
diplomatic office in Zagreb. "Croats know who Veljko Knezevic 
is.... As an arrogant chief of the central committee -- as well 
as the chief of SDB [State Security Service] operations -- he 
was tasked with creating political conditions in Croatia that 
would benefit the Serbs, both natives of Croatia and newcomers," 
SLOBODNA DALMACIJA states, adding that the return of Knezevic to 
the "scene of the crime" and the forcing of Croats to accept a 
"criminal" as "ambassador" contains "Milosevic's true message of 
reconciliation and forgiveness." The paper remarks that, with 
this appointment, Milosevic, the "Belgrade mass murderer," shows 
a sense of humor typical of "sadistic maniacs" who in 
"committing their crimes ridicule their victims." 

</TEXT>

