<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO in Position To Identify Planes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103133194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1205 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 1 March (TANJUG) -- Commenting on the 
downing of planes near Banja Luka yesterday, FRY [Federal 
Republic of Yugoslavia] President Zoran Lilic said today that 
"not a single aircraft has flown toward Bosnia-Herzegovina from 
FRY territory for two years now, i.e, since the FRY was set up." 
  In reply to a question about the incident near Banja Luka, 
Lilic pointed out that NATO was in the best position to say what 
had happened because NATO used AWACS monitoring systems that 
should know where the planes took off and where they landed. 
Lilic said that the FRY was against the use of force regardless 
of who used it. 

</TEXT>

