<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Hebron Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103160794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1535 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Mar 1 (TANJUG) -- The Foreign Ministry of 
the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (F.R.Y.) on Tuesday strongly 
condemned the recent unprovoked terrorist act in the mosque in 
Hebron which caused many innocent Palestinian casualties. 
  This senseless act has struck a fierce blow to the 
Palestinian-Israeli peace process, the Foreign Ministry said in 
a statement and added that it was in the interest of the people 
of Palestine and Israel to do everything in order to avoid that 
this incident leads to the increase of tension and escalation of 
the conflict. 
  Consistent to the principles of the peaceful resolution of 
conflicts as the only way to effectively solve problems in the 
international community, the F.R.Y. underscores the importance 
of continuing peace talks between Israel and the PLO with the 
aim of establishing a just and stable peace in the Middle East, 
the statement said. 

</TEXT>

