<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   FRY Bans Overflights of Macedonian Airplanes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103220294 Skopje Radio Macedonia Network in Macedonian 
2100 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje Radio Macedonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Macedonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Urban Planning, Civil Engineering, 
Transport, and Ecology today received a letter from the relevant 
bodies of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia [FRY] saying that, 
as of 2 March, airplanes belonging to the majority of Macedonian 
airlines will be banned from overflying Yugoslav territory. 
This refers to Palair-Macedonia [Macedonian flag-carrier], 
Vardar-Air, Macedonia-As, Avio-Impex, Meta, and Falcon. The 
reason for the ban, as the letter says, is the huge outstanding 
debt for the servicing of these airlines' overflights. 
  We have learned from our ministry that contact with Yugoslav 
bodies was established; they were called on to postpone the 
implementation of the decision by at least one month in order to 
enable the companies to repay their debts. 
  The letter also says that the same measure was applied to 
airlines from Bulgaria and Turkey that have incurred arrears in 
payments. 

</TEXT>

