<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greeks Allow Some Trucks To Cross Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203163394 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0203163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Border Partially Deblocked"] </F>
  [Text] Seven foreign vehicles that had been waiting for 2 
weeks to leave Greece were allowed to enter Macedonia [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] two days ago: 
Two Holland lorries carrying textile, two Italian trucks with 
raw materials for the leather industry, and three Greek trucks 
carrying oranges and olives for Macedonia. Four fuel-carrying 
vehicles of the firm Mlaz from Bogdanci were also permitted to 
leave Greece. 
  Two additional freight-cars loaded with phosphates for 
metallurgic industry in Titov Veles also arrived in Macedonia 
from the Greek railway station Idomeni yesterday. The remaining 
18,000 tons of phosphates left from Salonika for Burgas, 
Bulgaria. 

</TEXT>

