<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Workers Threaten Strike, `Massive' Protests </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203163994 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0203163994 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Protest Postponed for 8 Days"] </F>
  [Text] About 3,000 workers protested in front of the 
Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
Parliament yesterday. The workers' delegation was received by 
representatives of the parliament deputy groups and the Minister 
of Health and Social Politics Iliaz Sabriu also joined the 
meeting later on. 
  After the talks the workers from insolvent firms decided to 
postpone the general strike until next Tuesday, thus leaving 
additional 8 days for the Government to meet their demands. If 
no solution is offered by then, the workers announced massive 
protest marches. 

</TEXT>

