Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Government Session"] </F>
  [Text] At its yesterday session, the Macedonian Government 
determined the program on supporting the development of 
agriculture in 1994. The planned irretrievable sum of 75 
million denars will be used for the creation of artificial 
fields, development of the cattle breeding and the fishing in 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], 
financing of small accumulating dams, and so on. The government 
also proposed regulations in founding donator and charitable 
funds. 

