<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Reports Serb Attacks Around Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203122994 Paris AFP in English 1151 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0203122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, March 2 (AFP) -- A UN spokesman reported 
fighting Wednesday [2 March] within the 20-kilometre (12-mile) 
artillery exclusion zone around Sarajevo. 
  UN Protection Force (UNPROFOR) Canadian Lieutenant-Colonel 
Bill Aikman said there were reports that Bosnian Serb forces had 
attacked near the town of Vrbovik in the northwest part of the 
exclusion zone. The report was confirmed by UN military 
observers and Canadian reconnaissance troops. 
  The mainly Moslem Bosnian Army said Serbs had fired 
artillery 
from within the exclusion zone. Aikman said it was possible the 
artillery fire had come from outside the zone and that UN troops 
were investigating this. 
  Aikman said the NATO-mandated artillery withdrawal from in 
and around Sarajevo and a ceasefire in effect since February 9 
were being generally observed although there were minor 
violations. 

</TEXT>

