<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Warns Against `Illegal Gatherings' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203182394 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0203182394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Public Order Ministry spokesman reports that 
various political left-extermist forces continuously call for 
and incite illegal gatherings through their newspapers, 
particularly the Socialist Party with ZERI I POPULLIT. Such 
calls have increased greatly recently, on the eve of the trial 
of Fatos Nano, Ramiz Alia, and other blocmen. 
  The Public Order Ministry reports that it will act with the 
force of law against anyone who seeks to exert pressure on 
Albanian justice, which has an independent and inviolable power. 
At the same time, it undertakes to guarantee order, calm, and 
stability for the organs of justice, so that they can develop 
their legal activity as normally as possible. 
  The Public Order Ministry warns all violators, whoever they 
are, that they will be responsible before the law. 

</TEXT>

