<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hospitals Reportedly Full </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0203163794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0203163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic] </F>
  [Text] The Serbian aggressor this morning resumed 
artillery-infantry attacks on the Bihac region. Defenders at 
(Vlasko), Hasino Brdo, and Grmusko-Srbljanski Heights have been 
submitted to unprecedented howitzer and tank fire, which has 
killed a large number of them. Although they have been 
suffering constant losses in manpower and military hardware, the 
chetniks are still mindlessly attacking. Heroes of the 5th 
Corps have destroyed one enemy antiaircraft gun, two ZIS 
weapons, and several motor vehicles, which obviously serves the 
chetniks with a reason to continue and increase their wild 
artillery activity on Bihac, Cazin, and their outskirts. There 
are dozens of injured civilians due to the systematic 
destruction of settlements over the last 24 hours. Local 
hospitals are full, and there are hardly any basic first aid 
kits. Chetnik helicopters are still freely flying over the 
Bihac area bringing in new manpower and new artillery. The 
world is still calmly observing this [word indistinct] and 
disappearance of people and tows from the face of the earth. 

</TEXT>

