<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Refuses To Register New Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203151894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Interior Ministry has turned down the 
application for the registration of a new right-wing party, the 
Democratic Union [Demokraticka Unie]. Milah Hulik, member of 
the preparatory committee, said that the application was turned 
down because only 700 out of a total of 1,570 signatures 
supplied were accepted. The law requires at least 1,000 
signatures for a political party to be registered. Allegedly, 
another reason for the decision was certain unusual features in 
the Democratic Union's program. 
  Milan Hulik was hopeful that the reasons for turning down 
the 
application would be removed and that the new right-wing party 
would be registered as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

