<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romanian Prime Minister Begins One-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303124194 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0303124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu, heading a 
Romanian government delegation, has begun a one-day official 
visit in Bratislava at the invitation of his Slovak counterpart 
Vladimir Meciar. At this hour the two delegations, headed by 
the Slovak and the Romanian prime ministers, are holding a first 
round of talks, our correspondent, Pavel Mocanu, reports. 
  Today at 1030, at the headquarters of Slovakia's Council of 
Ministers, the Romanian guests were received by Prime Minister 
Meciar, Jozef Prokes, deputy chairman of the Council of 
Ministers, and other members of the government. The agenda of 
the visit also includes meetings with Slovak President Michal 
Kovac and Parliament Speaker Ivan Gasparovic. 
  Following the conclusion of their talks, the two prime 
ministers are to sign a memorandum on the liberalization of 
commercial ties between Romania and Slovakia and accords on the 
avoidance of double taxation and the mutual promotion and 
protection of investments. 
  Flying over the territory of Hungary, Vacaroiu sent a 
telegram to his Hungarian counterpart, Boross, cordially 
greeting him and wishing prosperity for the Hungarian people. 

</TEXT>

