<H3> <TI>   Krajina Minister Says Downed Aircraft Croatian </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0303143594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1320 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0303143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 3 March (TANJUG) -- Slobodan Jarcevic, 
minister of foreign affairs of the republic of Serb Krajina, 
told TANJUG today he "believed that aircraft that were downed 
above Bosnia were sent by Croatian Government and the Croatian 
Army leadership." 
  Jarcevic said that Croats and Muslims were for months 
fighting in central Bosnia and that the Croatian forces 
continuously bombarded Muslim positions. 
  "Therefore, the aircraft were most probably Croatian, 
because 
the Serbs do not fight there," Jarcevic added stressing that the 
aircraft were downed above the area of the Croat-Muslim 
conflicts. 

</TEXT>

